- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with the concept of borders in strings, which is a fundamental concept in formal language theory.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper uses probabilistic arguments to prove a lower bound on the length of the maximal unbordered factor of a string.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses probabilistic arguments, which are often used in machine learning.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of computing the maximal unbordered factor of a string.
